Class Summary
AePlayWave This class is used to play sounds in-game.
AWPBullet represents the bullet fired from the TAWP when it's equipped to the player
Backdrop Represents the Background in the game
FileOpener Used to open, prompt to open, save, prompt to save and read files.
GameScreen Draws any current game going on.
GroundHole Represents a hole in the ground that Things in the game can fall through and die.
Hero  
LevelEditor The Level Editor part of the game.
MainScreen  
PauseScreen Represents the screen that comes up when there is a current game and is paused.
Room This represents a room that contains all of the Things that are in the game.
Screen This represents an in-game Screen.
ScreenController This class controls the ScreenManager.
ScreenManager This class holds all the Screens to be displayed in the game and also switches to/from them when necessary.
Serializer Helper class used to write levels to files.

The four arrays stored in this are properties of a Thing.
SinglePlayer This class actually plays through the levels that are created with LevelEditor.
SpawnScreen The most important feature of the Level Editor.
Sprite This is a helper class for manipulating images.
TAWP This represents an AWP Item.
TBGBlock Represents a TBlock that can be walked through
TBlock  
TBound Represents a bound that can't be passed BY ANYTHING!!!
TCape When equipped, the Hero gets the temporary ability to fly.
TColoredBlock Represents a Gridded Thing that has Color.
TEnemy Enemy in game.
TextButton Helper class used to draw Strings to the screen.
TGoal Represents the Goal the player must touch if he/she wants to win
TGoomba It's a Goomba.
TGridded  
Thing This represents an object that can be put in the game.
THorizontalBound An infinitely tall and 32-unit wide structure that impermeable by all in-game objects.
TItem This is an Item that can be spawned in game, can be equipped to a player and can be put inside TBlocks.
TKoopa This represents a Koopa in game.
TLinker links objects together so they can interact.
TMetalCap When equipped, the Hero can be hit by an enemy without dying.
TPipe A long green thing with a hole in the top.
TPirhana The little chomper dude that is found in pipes.
TRemover removes objects from the game
TSpawn Represents where the player should spawn in SinglePlayer
TStar When equipped, the player becomes invulerable for a short period of time and flashes seizure-inducing colors.
TTool Represents a tool used in the level editor.
TVerticalBound An infinitely wide and 32-unit tall structure that impermeable by all in-game objects.
TVisibleTool A tool that is not removed instantly from the room after creation.
Wuigi Stores game constants and initializes the game
